	<div itemprop="text"><p>Hi Otto, </p>
<p>Another translation question for you. A user who wanted to work on the german translation of thematic asked us: </p>
<p>&#8220;Should we include HTML-Entities for umlauts?&#8221;</p>
<p>And since I didn&#8217;t have the faintest idea I was hoping you could illuminate me.  Should translators use UTF-8 or HTML entities for accents and special characters?</p>
<p>Thanks,<br />
-Kathy</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/internationalization-youre-probably-doing-it-wrong/comment-page-1/?replytocom=11176#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-11176", "11176", "respond", "771")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
