		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2013-03-24T07:36:15+00:00">March 24, 2013 at 7:36 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Okay, you&#8217;re correct. Those elements are indeed read by core and used for the translation of the header parts of the plugin/theme. That behavior was added in 3.4, and so I&#8217;ve never really seen or used it.</p>
<p>However, they are not required elements by any means and translation of the rest of the plugin works perfectly fine without them. The only need for them is for translating those header elements. If you do not desire to translate those, then these two extra headers are wholly unnecessary.</p>
</div>

